{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"BeatsX are shit","content":"<!--more--><html><head></head><body><p>I don&#x2019;t usually write about products but I&#x2019;m so fed up with the BeatsX earphones that I need to tell others about it. In the one and a half years that I&#x2019;ve owned them, they&#x2019;ve broken&#xA0;<strong>three times</strong>&#xFEFF;. Luckily I haven&#x2019;t had to pay for a single repair, but the process of exchanging it is starting to become time consuming and really annoying.</p>\n\n<p>I purchased my BeatsX back in February 2017. I fell in love with them right away; the wirelessness meant I didn&#x2019;t have to deal with tangling cords, and because they were in-ear I could listen to podcasts even on loud commutes.</p>\n\n<p>Little did I know how fragile they were. Let me tell you about my BeatsX woes&#x2026;</p>\n\n<h3>Incident #1: November 2017</h3>\n\n<p>The first time my BeatsX broke was when I was in Japan. All of a sudden it stopped connecting to any of my devices. I later found out that this was a common issue, as I saw multiple threads on Reddit and Apple Support forum posts about it. On this same trip both my iPhone (camera stopped working) and Macbook (battery stopped charging) had broken so I was already pretty pissed off.</p>\n\n<p>I couldn&#x2019;t take them for repairs anywhere in Naha so I had to wait until I got home to Montreal before I could do anything. I also refused to buy one of those overpriced 3.5mm-to-Lightning adapters. All of this made for an extremely boring plane ride back to Montreal.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter border--gray\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 90.63324538258576%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image wp-image-6759\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"work authorization 1\" title src=\"/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/dbb61/work-authorization-1.png\" srcset=\"/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/19bd1/work-authorization-1.png 163w,\n/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/d3bcb/work-authorization-1.png 325w,\n/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/dbb61/work-authorization-1.png 650w,\n/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/6b691/work-authorization-1.png 975w,\n/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/91670/work-authorization-1.png 1300w,\n/static/71b2fa3cb26ca00fa53933672217bbfe/e1ff9/work-authorization-1.png 1516w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></figure>\n\n<h3>Incident #2: March 2018</h3>\n\n<p>Several months had gone by and I had almost forgotten about the first incident, when suddenly the right earbud started to crackle. Shortly after the right earbud stopped working entirely, and I had to make yet another trip to the Apple Store.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image aligncenter border--gray\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 88.59416445623343%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image wp-image-6760\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"work authorization 2\" title src=\"/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/dbb61/work-authorization-2.png\" srcset=\"/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/19bd1/work-authorization-2.png 163w,\n/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/d3bcb/work-authorization-2.png 325w,\n/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/dbb61/work-authorization-2.png 650w,\n/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/6b691/work-authorization-2.png 975w,\n/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/91670/work-authorization-2.png 1300w,\n/static/01196581ab81fe458570440bf0af5522/d654f/work-authorization-2.png 1508w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></figure>\n\n<p>Thankfully, the Apple staff replaced my headphones free of charge because I&#x2019;d just gotten them replaced in November.</p>\n\n<h3>Incident #3: July 2018</h3>\n\n<p>The third incident happened again while I was traveling, this time in Toronto. Once again, the right earbud started crackling and lost output.</p>\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 650px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 43.64060676779463%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n    <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image wp-image-6785\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"repair status\" title src=\"/static/14fb62174f0fa0b7c78bee12a6919ec5/dbb61/repair-status.png\" srcset=\"/static/14fb62174f0fa0b7c78bee12a6919ec5/19bd1/repair-status.png 163w,\n/static/14fb62174f0fa0b7c78bee12a6919ec5/d3bcb/repair-status.png 325w,\n/static/14fb62174f0fa0b7c78bee12a6919ec5/dbb61/repair-status.png 650w,\n/static/14fb62174f0fa0b7c78bee12a6919ec5/ab944/repair-status.png 857w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\">\n  </span></figure>\n\n<p>I called Apple support and luckily the Apple support staff was super understanding. He offered to send me a new pair even though mine were out of warranty by a long shot. The silver lining in all of this is that Apple&#x2019;s support is awesome.</p>\n\n<hr class=\"wp-block-separator\">\n\n<p>I&#x2019;m so disappointed with the quality of the BeatsX. They are awesome when they work but it really sucks having to get them replaced so often. For ~$200 CAD I shouldn&#x2019;t have to worry about them breaking all the time.</p>\n\n<p>If you&#x2019;re considering buying a pair of BeatsX earphones, I&#x2019;d think twice. They are fragile as hell and break even with regular use.</p>\n</body></html>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"beatsx-are-shit"}}